articles.description: James Palmer Jr. scored 24 of his 26 points in the second half, Isaiah Roby had all 11 of his after half, and Nebraska held off Maryland 70-66 on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Palmer's big 2nd half lifts Huskers past Maryland 70-66

images.caption: Nebraska's James Palmer Jr. flies up the court and throws down a massive, one-handed dunk in the face of Maryland's Kevin Huerter. Tempers flare at the other end of the court.
images.name: Nebraska's Palmer dunks all over his defender

articles.description: Kassius Robertson scored 16 points, Jordan Barnett added 15 and Missouri defeated No. 21 Texas A&M 62-58 to push its winning streak to five games Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Missouri edges No. 21 Texas A&M 62-58

images.caption: Guard Kassius Robertson talks about Mizzou's team effort in an upset win against No. 21 Texas A&M.
images.name: Defense, toughness making the difference for Tigers

articles.description: Fatts Russell intercepts a Richmond pass and takes it all the way to the rack for the easy layup.
articles.headline: URI's Russell goes coast-to-coast

images.caption: Fatts Russell intercepts a Richmond pass and takes it all the way to the rack for the easy layup.
images.name: URI's Russell goes coast-to-coast

articles.description: Arkansas head coach Mike Anderson talks about what the bench was able to provide and how the Hogs got it done defensively against Ole Miss.
articles.headline: Anderson: 'Real proud with the effort of our guys'

images.caption: Arkansas head coach Mike Anderson talks about what the bench was able to provide and how the Hogs got it done defensively against Ole Miss.

articles.description: Jeremy Harris had 24 points and Wes Clark scored 19, including three 3-pointers, to help Buffalo beat Kent State 84-72 on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Harris, Clark help Buffalo beat Kent State 84-72
Kentucky hoping to get rolling with visit to No. 10 Auburn

images.caption: SEC Network's Mike Morgan discusses what he expects to see from the Tigers and Wildcats when they match up.
images.name: Auburn, Kentucky looking to show how good they can be
